      1          /**
      2           *  @file       
      3           *
      4           *  @brief      Source file for the StatusLed module.
      5           *
      6           *  @details    Handles blinking the status led to indicate the health of the micro.
      7           *              The Fast Flash profile will always run for a defined amount of time at micro power up.
      8           *              Afterwards, the system inputs are used to determine the profile that will be used to drive the led.
      9           *              STATUS_LED_FEATURE                      - ENABLED to enable StatusLed feature
     10           *              STATUS_LED_VIRTUAL_PIN_INDEX            - StatusLed Pin index from VirtualPin table, starting from index 0 (instead of 1)
     11           *                                                        Mandatory if StatusLed feature is ENABLED
     12           *              STATUS_LED_ACTIVE_LOW                   - if ENABLED, Led will set Low to turn it ON. Default is DISABLED
     13           *              STATUS_LED_VIRTUAL_PIN_INDEX_INVALID()  - Macro to define function to call if Virtual Pin index is not valid
     14           *              STATUS_LED_RESUME_TIME_MS               - Time (in ms) to automatically resume Led blink after a StatusLed__Suspend()
     15           *                                                          Default is 0 - Disabled; Led will be resumed when StatusLed__Resume() is called
     16           *                                                          Maximum allowed is 2550.
     17           *              STATUS_LED_DEFAULT_COMM_NODE            - Overrides default node to check for Communication Failure event
     18           *                                                          Default values if not defined:
     19           *                                                          - WIN_UI_ADDRESS for ACU P3 and HMI Expansions only
     20           *                                                          - WIN_ACU_ADDRESS for MCU or ACU Expansions only
     21           *                                                          - Feature Disabled (REVEAL_BROADCAST_NODE, 15) for all other nodes
     22           *
     23           *
     24           *
     25           *  @copyright  Copyright 2017-$Date$. Whirlpool Corporation. All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL
     26           */
